### Deleting a Document using Ragie Class (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/ragieai/ragie-typescript/blob/main/docs/sdks/documents/README.md

This snippet demonstrates how to delete a specific document using the `Ragie` class. It initializes the `Ragie` client with an authentication token and then calls the `documents.delete` method, specifying the `documentId` and `partition` for the document to be removed. The result of the operation is logged to the console.

```TypeScript
import { Ragie } from "ragie";

const ragie = new Ragie({
  auth: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>"
});

async function run() {
  const result = await ragie.documents.delete({
    documentId: "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
    partition: "acme_customer_id"
  });

  // Handle the result
  console.log(result);
}

run();
```

