### Deleting a Document using Standalone Function (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/ragieai/ragie-typescript/blob/main/docs/sdks/documents/README.md

This snippet illustrates how to delete a document using the standalone `documentsDelete` function from `ragie/funcs/documentsDelete.js` for better tree-shaking. It initializes `RagieCore` once and passes its instance to the `documentsDelete` function along with the `documentId` and `partition`. It includes error handling for the operation's result.

```TypeScript
import { RagieCore } from "ragie/core.js";
import { documentsDelete } from "ragie/funcs/documentsDelete.js";

// Use `RagieCore` for best tree-shaking performance.
// You can create one instance of it to use across an application.
const ragie = new RagieCore({
  auth: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>"
});

async function run() {
  const res = await documentsDelete(ragie, {
    documentId: "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
    partition: "acme_customer_id"
  });

  if (!res.ok) {
    throw res.error;
  }

  const { value: result } = res;

  // Handle the result
  console.log(result);
}

run();
```

