### Listing Documents with Ragie SDK in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/ragieai/ragie-typescript/blob/main/docs/sdks/documents/README.md

This snippet demonstrates how to list documents using the Ragie SDK. It initializes the Ragie client with an authentication token and then calls the `documents.list` method, applying a filter for 'department' and a 'partition'. The results are iterated asynchronously page by page, logging each page to the console.

```TypeScript
import { Ragie } from "ragie";

const ragie = new Ragie({
  auth: "<YOUR_BEARER_TOKEN_HERE>",
});

async function run() {
  const result = await ragie.documents.list({
    filter: "{\"department\":{\"$in\":[\"sales\",\"marketing\"]}}",
    partition: "acme_customer_id",
  });

  for await (const page of result) {
    // Handle the page
    console.log(page);
  }
}

run();
```

